CatDescriptText: Cutline for image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 10, 1957, pg. 21, reads: "New Car Wash - The crew at the new P & R Fast Car Wash, which recently opened for business at 2929 Wylie Ave., is putting the finishing touches on a car just washed.  The brainchild of Eli Randolph and Norman Palmer, owners, the new car wash is a much-needed commodity in this area.  'We plan to give the best service,' Mr. Palmer said.  'Since opening we have been pleased with the support we've received.' Call MUseum 2-8500. - Harris Photo. - Adv.
TitMainTitle: Men wiping down Oldsmobile car at R and P (or P & R) Fast Car Wash, 2929 Wylie Avenue, Hill District
